      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@ScottCarlson thanks but the settings in the IDE are generelly only affecting the run configurations of the IDE. If you enter some commands into a terminal (even that of the IDE) it will pick up the JDK that is set in the system environment variables of Windows, and not the JDK you&#39;ve set in IntelliJ for your project."
